main event: An object observed coming down by parachute on Santa Catalina Island was recovered and turned over to the Air Force for identification.
interesting points: The object was identified as originating from the U.S.C.F.,The object's weight is reported to be about 15 lbs and is described as pale purplish-yellow,It has a parachute of 15 feet in diameter with alternating colors of gold and white,Markings on the object indicate it was manufactured in December 1960,There are recommendations for appropriate action to deactivate the device if necessary.
witness description: Lt. DCAS FT officer who telephoned in the report
